HEADWORD: faggot
<hw>fag"got</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧g"⟦ucr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[perh.
from <ets>fagot{5}</ets>, a shriveled old woman.]</ety> <def>a male
homosexual; -- always used disparagingly and considered offensive.</def>
<mark>[Slang, disparaging]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fagot, fag, fairy, pansy, queer, poof, poove,
pouf.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a bundle of sticks and branches bound together; --
